{{About|a list of rivers in Michigan|the community in Standish Township, Arenac County|Pine River, Michigan|the township in Gratiot County|Pine River Township, Michigan}} [[File:Pine Rivers Map US MI.svg|right|350px]] '''Pine River''' may refer to any of the following streams in the U.S. state of Michigan:
# [[Pine River (Alcona County, Michigan)]]. The main branch forms with the confluence of the East<ref>{{gnis|625144|East Branch Pine River (Alcona County)}}</ref> and West<ref>{{gnis|1616061|West Branch Pine River}}</ref> Branches of the Pine River at {{coord|44|29|38|N|83|23|16|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}} in [[Alcona County, Michigan|Alcona County]]. The South Branch<ref>{{gnis|638305|South Branch Pine River (Alcona County}}</ref> joins approximately {{convert|1.5|mi|km}} to the south and flows into [[Iosco County, Michigan|Iosco County]], where it empties into [[Van Etten Lake]] at {{Coord|44|29|38|N|83|23|16|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}} northwest of [[Oscoda, Michigan|Oscoda]].<ref>{{gnis|634987|Pine River (Iosco/Alcona Counties}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Arenac County, Michigan)]]. The main branch is formed by the confluence of the North<ref>{{gnis|633532|North Branch Pine River (Arenac County)}}</ref> and Middle<ref>{{gnis|632238|Middle Branch Pine River}}</ref> Branches northeast of [[Standish, Michigan|Standish]] and flows into the [[Saginaw Bay]] of Lake Huron at {{Coord|43|58|32|N|83|51|16|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|634985|Pine River (Arenac County)}}</ref> The South Branch Pine River joins the main stream at {{coord|43|59|08|N|83|53|17|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|638304|South Branch Pine River}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Charlevoix County, Michigan)]] is a short waterway, which along with Round Lake, connects [[Lake Charlevoix]] with Lake Michigan at [[Charlevoix, Michigan|Charlevoix]].<ref>{{gnis|634986|Pine River (Charlevoix County)}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Mackinac County)]] rises in [[Chippewa County, Michigan|Chippewa County]] and flows south through [[Mackinac County, Michigan|Mackinac County]] into the [[St. Martin Bay]] of Lake Huron at {{Coord|46|03|09|N|84|39|22|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}<ref>{{gnis|1621249|Pine River (Mackinac County)}}</ref> The North Pine River, also known as the North Branch Pine River, joins at {{coord|46|12|20|N|84|36|17|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|1621054|North Pine River}}</ref> Another tributary, Hemlock Creek, is also known as Pine River.<ref>{{gnis|1620167|Hemlock Creek}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Manistee River)]], also known as the South Branch Manistee River, rises in southeast [[Wexford County, Michigan|Wexford County]], flows southwest across northwest [[Osceola County, Michigan|Osceola County]], then west and north through the northeast corner of [[Lake County, Michigan|Lake County]] and back into southwest Wexford County, emptying into the [[Tippy Dam]] Pond on the [[Manistee River]] at {{Coord|44|13|37|N|85|54|27|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|1621248|Pine River (Manistee River)}}</ref> The main stream is formed from the confluence of the East Branch Pine River<ref>{{gnis|1619806|East Branch Pine River (Osceola County)}}</ref> with the North Branch Pine River (also known as the Little Pine River)<ref>{{gnis|1621033|North Branch Pine River}}</ref> at {{coord|44|06|02|N|85|31|40|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}. Another tributary, the Spaulding Creek, is also known as the Little Pine River<ref>{{gnis|1621713|Spalding Creek}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Marquette County)]], in [[Marquette County, Michigan|Marquette County]], is a very short stream draining Pine Lake into Lake Superior at {{Coord|46|53|27|N|87|52|13|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}, north of the [[Huron Mountains]].<ref>{{gnis|634983|Pine River (Marquette County)}}</ref> # [[Pine River (Chippewa River)]] rises in from Pine Lake in eastern [[Mecosta County, Michigan|Mecosta County]], flows mostly south and east through [[Isabella County, Michigan|Isabella County]], then south along eastern edge of [[Montcalm County, Michigan|Montcalm County]], then east and north through [[Gratiot County, Michigan|Gratiot County]] and [[Midland County, Michigan|Midland County]], emptying into the [[Chippewa River (Michigan)|Chippewa River]] at {{Coord|43|36|06|N|84|17|33|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}, just about two miles before it joins the [[Tittabawassee River]] near [[Midland, Michigan|Midland]].<ref>{{gnis|634984|Pine River (Midland County)}}</ref> The South Branch Pine River joins the main stream at {{coord|43|30|37|N|85|00|02|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}<ref>{{gnis|638303|South Branch Pine River (Isabella County)}}</ref> Another tributary, Miller Creek, is also sometimes known as Pine River or the West Branch Pine River.<ref>{{gnis|632364|Miller Creek}}</ref> The North Branch Pine River joins the main stream at {{coord|43|26|03|N|84|50|18|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|633531|North Branch Pine River (Montcalm County)}}</ref> # [[Pine River (St. Clair River)]] empties into the [[St. Clair River]] at {{Coord|42|49|13|N|82|29|08|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}} on the south side of [[St. Clair, Michigan|St. Clair]].<ref>{{gnis|1624827|Pine River (St. Clair County)}}</ref> The South Branch Pine River joins the main stream at {{coord|42|58|11|N|82|37|10|W|region:US-MI_type:river_source:GNIS}}.<ref>{{gnis|1624941|South Branch Pine River (St. Clair County)}}</ref> Another tributary, Quakenbush Drain, is also sometimes known as Pine River.<ref>{{gnis|1624851|Quakenbush Drain}}</ref> # [[Pine Creek (Ontanagon County, Michigan)]] empties into Lake Superior and is also known as the Pine River.<ref>{{gnis|1624213|Pine Creek (Ontanagon County)}}</ref>
There are also at least seventeen streams known as "Pine Creek" in Michigan which may sometimes be referred to as Pine River, as well some other variants.<ref>[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:2:::NO::P1_FNAME,P1_CLASS,P1_STATE:Pine Creek,Stream,Michigan GNIS Search Results], U.S. Geological Survey Geographical Names Information System: Pine Creek</ref>
