The '''Skadar-Peć Fault''' is a fault in [[Albania]] and [[Kosovo]]. It strikes NE-SW between the cities of [[Shkodër]] and [[Peć]].<ref name=Hrvatovic>{{cite book|last1=Hrvatović|first1=Hazim|title=Geologic Guidebook through Bosnia and Hercegovina|date=2005|publisher=Geological Survey Sarajevo|location=Sarajevo|isbn=9789958935138}}</ref> The fault marks the southern limit of the external nappes of the Dinarides, which crop out in the north-west. In the south-east the fault borders the internal nappes of the Dinarides.<ref name=Hrvatovic /><ref name=Leeuw>{{cite journal|last1=de Leeuw|first1=Arjan|last2=Mandic|first2=Oleg|last3=Krijgsman|first3=Wout|last4=Kuiper|first4=Klaudia|last5=Hrvatović|first5=Hazim|title=Paleomagnetic and geochronologic constraints on the geodynamic evolution of the Central Dinarides|journal=Tectonophysics|volume=530-531|pages=286–298|doi=10.1016/j.tecto.2012.01.004}}</ref>
